# Place the llama-server binary and dylibs here before building.
#
# Download pre-built binaries from:
#   https://github.com/ggerganov/llama.cpp/releases
#
# macOS Apple Silicon (current setup):
#   1. Download llama-b*-bin-macos-arm64-kleidiai.tar.gz
#   2. Run: python3 scripts/extract-macos-binaries.py
#      (or manually extract llama-server + all *.dylib files)
#   3. Rename: llama-server -> llama-server-aarch64-apple-darwin
#
# Other platforms:
#   Windows x64 : llama-server-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc.exe
#   macOS Intel  : llama-server-x86_64-apple-darwin
#   Linux x64    : llama-server-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu
#
# To find the target triple of your current machine, run:
#   rustc -vV | grep host
